  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\ni used `[POST] /beacon/validators` to retrieve information about my validators in one request.\r\n\r\nThe POST recieves a list of pubkeys (e.g. 0xdeadbeef) and returns a list of validator information.\r\n\r\nThis endpoint seems to have gone with newer lighthouse versions.\r\nNow https://ethereum.github.io/eth2.0-APIs is in place\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nNew version i use is `Docker v0.3.0`\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nResponse of the lighthouse beacon is `[405] Method not allowed`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nReturn with a List of validators\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nsee above, try to issue a POST request with a List of pubkeys (of validators) on the given endpoint.\r\n\r\nQuestion: \r\n\r\n**How do i request multiple validator information within _one_ request?**\r\n\r\nI see following alternatives, involving the endpoint https://ethereum.github.io/eth2.0-APIs/#/Beacon/getStateValidator\r\n\r\n- GET ​/eth​/v1​/beacon​/states​/head​/validators​/0xdeadbeef\r\n- GET ​/eth​/v1​/beacon​/states​/0xdeadbeef/validators​/0xdeadbeef\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  \r\n",
